= Sourdough Pizza <pizza-sourdough>

This is a thick, chewy sourdough pizza. See the original recipe here:
#url("https://www.thedivinechef.com/post/quick-sourdough-pizza")

#v(1em)

#columns(2)[
  == Equipment

  - Oven
  - Baking tray#footnote[~Cast iron preferred. A #url[baking steel] may also prove
      helpful. My tray has an area of 465cm#super[2] (72in#super[2]); adjust the recipe to
      compensate.]
  - Large bowl
  - Small towel, large enough to cover said bowl
  - Dutch hook (recommended) or fork, for mixing

  *Yields 1 pizza.*

  *Warning:* This recipe is a @adv_hydration[high-hydration] recipe. Attempt at your own
  peril.

  #colbreak()

  == Ingredients

  === Dough
  - 240 grams (1 cup), active sourdough starter (100% hydration)
  - 170 grams (3/4 cup), warm water
  - 40 grams (3 tbsp.) olive oil
  - 275 grams (2 1/2 cups), bread flour#footnote[~While you _can_ use all-purpose flour,
      it will not work well, because this recipe is very chewy.]
  - 5 grams (1 tsp.) salt

  === Recommended Toppings

  - Tomato sauce
  - Shredded mozarrella
  - Pickled green olives
  - Turkey pepperoni
]

== Steps

+ Whisk starter, water, and oil together in bowl.
+ Add flour & salt. Mix until consistent, very wet.
+ Cover bowl with a damp towel. Let dough rise, 12-24 hours.
+ Preheat oven to 245°C (475°F).
+ Punch dough into pizza crust on baking sheet. Spray more oil or water on top.
+ Bake 20-25 minutes.
+ Remove pizza from tray. Add water to bottom of tray. Flip dough upside-down and reinsert
  to tray.
+ Add toppings.
+ Bake another 7-10 minutes, double-checking every 2–3 minutes.
+ Let pizza sit for 5 minutes before slicing.
